senses.sense: (botany) Any plant of the genus Iberis; a candytuft.
A type of wild mountain goat of the genus Capra, such as the species Capra ibex.
(heraldry) An imaginary creature with serrated horns, somewhat similar to the heraldic antelope.
Alternative form of ibid. ("in the same place")
Any of various long-legged wading birds in the family Threskiornithidae, having long downcurved bills used to probe the mud for prey such as crustaceans.
Ibidorhyncha struthersii, a species of wading bird in the monotypic family Ibidorhynchidae, inhabiting the shingle riverbanks of the high plateau of Central Asia and the Himalayas.
An insect-derived lubricating powder used in polishing.
(pharmaceutical drug) A synthetic compound used widely as an analgesic and anti-inflammatory drug.
(rare) To treat with ibuprofen; to administer ibuprofen to.
